Start a minikube

    minikube start

View nodes

    kubectl get nodes

Run an image
    
    kubectl run kubernetes-bootcamp --image=gcr.io/google-samples/kubernetes-bootcamp:v1 --port=8080

View deployments

    kubectl get deployments

View pods and the deployments name

    kubectl get pods

Delete a pod
    
    kubectl delete pod $POD_NAME

Delete a deployment
    
    kubectl delete deployment $DEPLOYMENT_NAME

To access the image, a proxy is needed

    kubectl proxy

View logs

    kubectl logs $POD_NAME

Enter the container

    kubectl exec -ti $POD_NAME bash

Inside the container is possible to access the application using curl command


    
